Global report

Piotr Bystranowski

2025-02-27

Sample

368 participants answered at least one question, while 234 participants completed the entire survey.

30 is the median number of employees in the participants’ organizations (max = 10^{5}, min = 0. 20 is the median number of lawyers in the participants’ organizations (max = 1.2^{4}, min = 0). 3 is the median number of laywers handling AI-based software for automating tasks considered specifically legal (max = 3000, min = 0). 1 is the median number of tech specialists handling AI-based software for automating tasks considered specifically legal (max = 150, min = 0).

The likelihood of an organization adopting a policy on the use of chatbots is predicted by its size, most prominently by the number of lawyers handling AI-based software for automating tasks considered specifically legal and, to a lesser degree, by the total number of employees, but not by the total number of lawyers or tech specialists handling AI-based software for automating tasks considered specifically legal. Another strong predictor is the organization advising clients or other departments on AI.
